{{Expand list|date=May 2012}}
[[File:Great-Lakes.svg|thumb|A map showing the [[Great Lakes]]]] [[File:RobertNoble.jpg|thumb|Populated islands are most commonly accessed by [[bridge]] or [[ferry]] boat, although some islands also have [[airports]] to facilitate air travel.]] [[File:Madeline Island 427.JPG|thumb|Tourism has helped the [[Downtown|downtown sector]] of many island communities, such as the business district of [[La Pointe, Wisconsin]], on [[Madeline Island]].]] {| class="infobox" style="font-size:88%;text-align:center;" | style="background:#ccf;" | '''Most populated islands''' |- |Grand Island (New York): 20,000 |- |Manitoulin Island: 13,000 |- |Grosse Ile: 11,000 |- |St. Joseph Island: 1,000 |- |Walpole Island: 1,800 |- |} The following is a list of '''populated islands of the [[Great Lakes]]''' and connecting rivers. The islands listed have a specified year-round population of over 50 residents.
Many islands are popular [[tourist destinations]], and experience a sharp population increase during peak travel seasons.
In 2017, the ''Great Lakes Island Coalition'' was founded, a group dedicated to representing the interests of Great Lakes island residents.<ref>{{cite web|title=Wksu.org/|url=http://wksu.org/term/great-lakes-island-coalition#stream/0|accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref> At an annual [[Summit (meeting)|summit]], related issues of discussion include environmental issues facing the Great Lakes island inhabitants, such as water levels and quality, [[invasive species]], and even government policy topics, such as nuclear water storage and shipment in the Great Lakes region.<ref>{{cite web|title=Manitoulin.ca/|url=http://www.manitoulin.ca/2018/01/17/great-lakes-islands-coalition-seeking-manitoulin-members/|accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref>
==Algonquin Island== {{Main|Toronto Islands}}
Part of the city of [[Toronto]], '''Algonquin Island''' is one of the Toronto Islands, an archipelago in [[Toronto Harbour]]. Unlike most of the archipelago, which is made up of parkland and amusement facilities, Algonquin Island is residential.
==Amherst Island== {{Main|Amherst Island}}
'''Amherst Island''' is, at 70 square kilometers, the largest island wholly within [[Lake Ontario]] (Wolfe Island is larger, but the eastern end of the island is in the [[St. Lawrence River]]). Amherst Island has a year-round population of 450, which grows slightly in the summer. The island, which is served by a ferry out of Millhaven, is entirely rural, and is located in [[Loyalist, Ontario|Loyalist Township]], [[Lennox and Addington County]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].
==Beaver Island== {{Main|Beaver Island (Lake Michigan)|}}
'''Beaver Island''' is the largest island in [[Lake Michigan]] and part of the Beaver Island [[archipelago]] of [[Michigan]] in the [[United States]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Beaver Island Website|url=http://www.beaverisland.net/|work=Website}}</ref> It lies about 32 miles (50&nbsp;km) from the city of [[Charlevoix, Michigan|Charlevoix]] on the mainland, and can be reached by air or boat. St. James is the name of the unincorporated community on the island, which has a population of 551.<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/DTTable?_bm=y&-context=dt&-ds_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U&-CHECK_SEARCH_RESULTS=N&-CONTEXT=dt&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_P001&-tree_id=4001&-redoLog=false&-transpose=N&-all_geo_types=N&-_caller=geoselect&-geo_id=06000US2602963140&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001009&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001010&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001011&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001012&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001013&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001014&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001015&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001016&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001017&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001018&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001019&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001020&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001021&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001022&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001023&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001024&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001025&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001026&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001027&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001028&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001029&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001030&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001031&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001032&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001033&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001034&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001035&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001036&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001037&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001038&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001039&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001040&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001041&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001042&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001045&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001046&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001047&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001048&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001079&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001080&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001081&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001082&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001083&-geo_id=100$10000US260299805001996&-search_results=15000US260299805001&-format=&-_lang=en&-show_geoid=Y Beaver Island: Peaine township and Saint James township Blocks 1009 through 1048, Blocks 1079 through 1083, Block 1996, Census Tract 9805, Charlevoix County, Michigan] United States Census Bureau</ref>
==Barrie Island== {{Main|Barrie Island|}}
The municipality of '''Gordon/Barrie Island''' is a township in [[Manitoulin District]] in Lake Huron in north central Ontario, Canada. The island has a significant summer recreational population. It is connected to [[Manitoulin Island]] by [[Highway 540A (Ontario)|Highway 540A]], which crosses the water via a [[causeway]] at the narrowest part of the strait.<ref>{{cite web|title=Barrie Island Website|url=http://www.gordonbarrieisland.ca/|work=Website}}</ref>
==Bois Blanc Island, Michigan== {{Main|Bois Blanc Island (Michigan)|}}
'''Bois Blanc Island''' is located in [[Lake Huron]] southeast of [[Mackinac Island]] and almost due north of the city of [[Cheboygan, Michigan]]. Plaunt Transportation is the sole provider of [[ferry]] services for the island.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bois Blanc Island Website|url=http://www.bois-blanc.com|work=Website}}</ref>
==Bois Blanc Island, Ontario== {{Main|Bois Blanc Island (Ontario)|}}
'''[[Bois Blanc Island (Ontario)|Bois Blanc Island]]''' is located in the [[Detroit River]]. It was previously the site of the [[Boblo Island Amusement Park]]. It is accessed by private ferry from [[Amherstburg, Ontario]] and has a winter population of 50 - 60.<ref>[http://detroit.cbslocal.com/2012/05/20/more-single-family-houses-to-be-built-on-bob-lo-island/ More Single Family Houses To Be Built On Bob-Lo Island], CBS Detroit, May 20, 2012</ref>
==Cayuga Island==
{{Main|Cayuga Island}}
'''Cayuga Island''' is part of the city of [[Niagara Falls, New York]], located in the [[Niagara River]] several miles upstream of the [[Niagara Falls|falls]] themselves. Part of the [[Niagara Falls, New York#LaSalle|LaSalle]] neighborhood, the island contains a mix of parkland and middle-class housing.
==Centre Island== {{Main|Toronto Islands}}
'''Centre Island''' is the largest of the Toronto Islands, an archipelago located in [[Toronto]]'s [[Toronto Harbour|harbour]] on [[Lake Ontario]]. Though most of the islands' residences and businesses were systematically removed beginning in 1953 in favor of parkland and other recreational facilities,<ref>{{cite web|title=Toronto Island Community: The Place of My Dreams|url=http://torontoisland.org/Home/BriefIslandHistory/tabid/120/Default.aspx|work=Website}}</ref> a small year-round community of several dozen houses remains at the east end of the island, known as Ward's Island.
==Cockburn Island== {{Main|Cockburn Island (Ontario)|}}
'''Cockburn Island''' is an [[island]] in the Canadian province of Ontario, located in the Manitoulin District. Most of the island is incorporated as the municipal [[township (Canada)|township]] of Cockburn Island. While having a low permanent population, its population grows significantly in the summer, to about 200 residents.<ref>{{cite web|title=City Data|url=http://www.city-data.com/canada/Cockburn-Island-Township.html|work=Website}}</ref>
==Drummond Island== {{Main|Drummond Island|}}
'''Drummond Island''' is one of the largest islands in [[Lake Huron]], and consists of [[Drummond Township, Michigan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Drummond Island Website|url=http://www.drummondislandchamber.com/|work=Website}}</ref> The [[unincorporated community|unincorporated area]] had a population of 992 residents as of the [[2000 United States Census|2000 Census]]. The island lies along the Canada–US border, and is adjacent to Manitoulin Island.
==Grand Island (Michigan)== {{main|Grand Island Township, Michigan|}}
'''Grand Island''' in Lake Superior has a population of 47 according to the 2010 Census. The island is in the U.S. state of Michigan's Upper Peninsula. Most of the island is a federal park.
==Grand Island (New York)== {{main|Grand Island, New York|}}
Located in the [[Niagara River]], '''Grand Island''' is located in [[Erie County, New York]] and is a suburb of the city of [[Buffalo, New York|Buffalo]] with a population of 20,374 as of the [[2010 United States Census|2010 Census]]. It is the most populated freshwater island in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|title=Moon Travel Guides: Grand Island|url=http://www.moon.com/destinations/new-york-state/western-new-york/buffalo/buffalo-excursions/grand-island|work=Website}}</ref>
==Grosse Ile== {{main|Grosse Ile (Michigan)|}}
'''Grosse Ile''' lies in the Detroit River, downriver from [[Detroit]]. It is part of [[Wayne County, Michigan]] and had a population over 10,000. The largest island in the Detroit River, it is one of the most populated islands in the Great Lakes system. It is reached by two bridges or a small airport.
==Harsens Island== {{main|Harsens Island|}}
'''Harsens Island''' is an island in the [[St. Clair River]] delta on the U.S. border opposite Canada's [[Walpole Island]]. It has a population of over 1,200 year-round residents and perhaps 5,000 in summer. It is served by Champion's Auto Ferry.
==Kelleys Island== {{Main|Kelleys Island, Ohio|}}
'''Kelleys Island''' is both a [[village (United States)#Ohio|village]] in [[Erie County, Ohio|Erie County]], [[Ohio]], [[United States]], and the island which it fully occupies in [[Lake Erie]]. <ref>{{cite web|title=Kelleys Island Website|url=http://www.kelleysislandchamber.com/|work=Website}}</ref> The population is 367.
==Mackinac Island== {{Main|Mackinac Island|}}
'''Mackinac Island''' is an island and tourist area covering 3.8 square miles in Lake Huron, located between the state of Michigan's [[Upper Peninsula of Michigan|Upper]] and [[Lower Peninsula of Michigan|Lower Peninsulas]]<ref>{{cite web|title= Macinac.Com|url=http://mackinac.com/|work=Website}}</ref>
==Madeline Island== {{Main|Madeline Island|}}
'''Madeline Island''' is located in [[Lake Superior]] and contains the town of [[La Pointe, Wisconsin|La Pointe]], with a population of 246. The island has a rich history and was once the home of a French [[fur trade|fur trading post]].<ref>{{cite web|title= MadelineIsland.Com|url=http://www.madelineisland.com/|work=Website}}</ref>
==Manitoulin Island== {{Main|Manitoulin Island|}}
'''Manitoulin Island''' is a Canadian island in Lake Huron, and is the largest island in a freshwater lake in the world. It has two incorporated towns, and eight townships with a population of 13,000, thus making it the most populated island in the Great Lakes.<ref>{{cite web|title=Manitoulin Island Website|url=http://manitoulin-island.com/|work=Website}}</ref>
==Middle Bass Island== {{main|Middle Bass Island|}}
'''Middle Bass Island''' is an Ohio island in western Lake Erie with a year-round population of 95. It lies near Kelleys Island and South Bass Island (Put-In-Bay). The island has an airport and is a stop on the inter-island ferry.
==Neebish Island== {{Main|Neebish Island|}}
'''Neebish Island''' is an island in the U.S. state of Michigan in the [[St. Marys River (Michigan-Ontario)|St. Marys River]] between the [[United States]] and the Canadian province of Ontario. There is one store and one church on the island, and a car ferry service operates April 1 to January 15.<ref>{{cite web|title=Neebish Island Website|url=http://neebishisland.com/|work=Website}}</ref>
==Pelee Island== {{Main|Pelee, Ontario}}
'''Pelee Island''' is the largest island in Lake Erie,<ref>{{cite web|title=Tourism Windsor Essex Pelee Island website|url=http://www.visitwindsoressex.com/wps/wcm/connect/twepi/twepi/main+nav/wineries+and+agri-tourism/wineries/pelee+island+winery|work=Website}}</ref> and is the southernmost populated place in Canada.<ref>[http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/windsor/story/2011/08/19/wdr-pelee-island-health-care.html Residents protest Pelee Island health care access], [[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]]</ref> It has a year-round population of 170 with much higher numbers in summer.
==South Bass Island== {{Main|South Bass Island|}}
'''South Bass Island''' is located in western Lake Erie, and a part of [[Ottawa County, Ohio]]. It contains the village of [[Put-in-Bay, Ohio|Put-in-Bay]], which has a population of 128 as of the [[2000 United States Census|2000 Census]]. [[Ferry]] service connects the community with [[Catawba Island Township, Ottawa County, Ohio|Catawba Island]], [[Kelleys Island, Ohio|Kelleys Island]], [[Port Clinton, Ohio|Port Clinton]], and [[Sandusky, Ohio]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Put-in-Bay Website|url=http://villageofpib.com/|work=Website}}</ref>
==St. Joseph Island== {{Main|St. Joseph Island (Ontario)}}
'''St. Joseph Island''' is a Canadian Island in Lake Huron, and is the second largest island in Lake Huron. It has a year-round population of around 2000, and is connected to the mainland by the [[Bernt Gilbertson]] Bridge spanning the [[North Channel (Ontario)|North Channel]] of Lake Huron along [[Ontario Highway 548|Highway 548]].<ref>{{cite web|title=St. Joseph Island Website|url=http://www.stjosephisland.net/|work=Website}}</ref>
==Sugar Island== {{Main|Sugar Island (Michigan)|}}
'''Sugar Island''' is an island in the U.S. state of Michigan in the [[St. Marys River (Michigan-Ontario)|St. Marys River]] between the United States and the Canadian province of Ontario. The entire island constitutes [[Sugar Island Township, Michigan|Sugar Island Township]] in [[Chippewa County, Michigan|Chippewa County]] at the eastern tip of the Upper Peninsula. According to the 2000 census, there were 683 people living on the island.<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/DTTable?_bm=y&-show_geoid=Y&-tree_id=4001&-_caller=geoselect&-context=dt&-errMsg=&-all_geo_types=N&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_G001&-redoLog=false&-transpose=N&-search_map_config=|b=50|l=en|t=4001|zf=0.0|ms=sel_00dec|dw=0.1447413419125896|dh=0.07565724625317631|dt=gov.census.aff.domain.map.EnglishMapExtent|if=gif|cx=-84.43320788259282|cy=45.74691039516325|zl=4|pz=4|bo=318:317:316:315:314:313:323:319|bl=362:393:392:358:357:356:355:354|ft=350:349:335:389:388:332:331|fl=381:403:204:380:369:379:368|g=06000US2609709500&-PANEL_ID=p_dt_geo_map&-_lang=en&-geo_id=06000US2603377020&-CONTEXT=dt&-format=&-search_results=06000US2609709500&-ds_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U Sugar Island Township, Chippewa County] United States Census Bureau</ref>
==Washington Island== {{Main|Washington Island (Wisconsin)|}}
'''Washington Island''' is located about 7 miles northeast of the tip of [[Door Peninsula]] in [[Door County, Wisconsin]]. The island has a year-round population of 660 people as of the 2000 Census.<ref>{{cite web|title=Washington Island Website|url=http://www.washingtonisland.com/|work=Website}}</ref> The unincorporated community of [[Detroit Harbor, Wisconsin|Detroit Harbor]] is located on the island.
==Walpole Island== {{main|Walpole Island|}}
'''Walpole Island''' ('''Bkejwanong''') lies on the Canadian side of the [[St. Clair River]] delta. It is the main part of Walpole Island 46 [[Indian reserve]] and has a population over 2,200. It neighbors the U.S. Harsens Island. It is accessible by bridge from the Canadian mainland and ferry from the U.S.
==Wolfe Island== {{Main|Wolfe Island (Ontario)|}}
'''Wolfe Island''' is an island located at the entrance to the Saint Lawrence River in Lake Ontario near [[Kingston, Ontario]]. The resident population is approximately 1400 people, but this number can double or triple during the summer months.<ref>{{cite web|title=Wolfe Island Website|url=http://www.wolfeisland.com/|work=Website}}</ref>
