{{Infobox mountain | name = Shimbiris | photo = | photo_caption = | map = Somalia | map_caption = Location of Shimbiris in Somalia | location = {{flag|Somalia}} | label_position = bottom | coordinates = {{coord|10|44|09|N|47|14|42|E|type:mountain_region:SO_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | elevation_m = 2460 | elevation_ref = <ref name="peaklist"/> | prominence_m = 1495 | prominence_ref = <ref name="peaklist">[http://peaklist.org/WWlists/ultras/africa.html List of African ultras on Peaklist.org – Somalia footnote] SRTM value of 2,460 m elevation. Prominence figure is based on this elevation. Retrieved 27 September 2011</ref> | listing = [[List of countries by highest point|Country high point]] | range = [[Ogo Mountains]] | topo = | range_coordinates = | coordinates_ref = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = | map_size = 220 }} '''Mount Shimbiris''' is the highest [[Summit (topography)|peak]] in [[Somalia]].<ref name="peaklist"/> It has an elevation of {{convert|2460|m|ft|0}} above sea level.<ref name="SATG">{{cite web|title=Al-Madow Mountain Forest|url=http://satg.org/?s=madow/|publisher=SATG|accessdate=15 May 2014}}</ref> It is located in the [[Cal Madow|Al Madow mountain range]] in northern Somalia in the [[Sanaag]] region. [[SRTM]] data shows that its often-quoted elevation of {{convert|2416|m}} is slightly low.<ref name="peaklist"/>
There is no vehicle access. However, visitors can stay in a tent. <ref>{{cite web|title=Mountain Forecast|url=http://www.mountain-forecast.com/peaks/Shimbiris|accessdate=27 January 2017}}</ref>
