{{Unreferenced|date=November 2008}}

'''Podlužje''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|Подлужје}}) is a small geographical region in [[Serbia]]. It is located in south-eastern [[Syrmia]]. The western part of Podlužje belong to the autonomous province of [[Vojvodina]], and the eastern part belongs to the city of [[Belgrade]]. The Serbian Orthodox [[Fenek monastery]] and natural reserve [[Obedska Pond]] are situated in this region, as well as the medieval town of [[Kupinovo|Kupinik]] (today a village named Kupinovo), the former seat of the Serbian despots in Syrmia.

